main event: Two radar targets were observed traveling parallel at 5-6 miles apart, maintaining constant position and distance from each other before disappearing together.
interesting points: The targets displayed an indication of a 'Joining' or 'splitting' maneuver as the radar indicated that the targets had already exploded into two objects.
An Air Force aircraft was investigating the objects, but had no contact.
The targets were initially classified as possibly being a balloon or aircraft, but the conclusion was 'Unknown'.
The sighting occurred on June 22, with the time of observation being 1600-1615 hrs.
